name: okefenokee-national-wildlife-refuge-annual-narrative-report-calendar-year-1981
notes: This annual narrative report for Okefenokee and Banks Lake National Wildlife Refuges summarizes refuge activities during the 1981 calendar year.  The report begins with a summary of the yearu2019s highlights and climatic conditions.   Land acquisition-including fee title is also covered.  The report includes a planning section which discusses master plan, management plan, public participation, research and investigations.  Refuge administration is outlined; information about personnel, funding, safety, technical assistance, and other items is given.  Habitat management is also covered.  Subjects include general, wetlands, forests, fire management, pest control, wilderness and special areas.  The wildlife section of the report discusses wildlife diversity, endangered and/or threatened species, waterfowl, marsh and water birds, shorebirds, gulls, terns, and allied species, raptors, other migratory birds, game mammals, other resident wildlife, fisheries resources, marking and banding.  The public uses of the refuge described in this report include general, outdoor classrooms - students, outdoor classrooms - teachers, interpretive foot trails, interpretive foot routes, interpretive exhibits/demonstrations, hunting, fishing, wildlife observation, other wildlife oriented recreation, camping, picnicking, other non-wildlife oriented recreation, law enforcement, youth programs, cooperating associations, concessions, and volunteer programs.  The equipment and facilities section of the report provides information about new construction, rehabilitation, major maintenance,.  Items of interest are provided at the end.
title: Okefenokee National Wildlife Refuge : Annual Narrative Report : Calendar Year 1981
